# Learned-Memory Maintenance

Follow `docs/policy/agents-md-policy.md` for the full policy. Key rules:

- Keep `AGENTS.md` under 150 lines, each section under 50 lines (Nx-managed block at the tail is exempt and auto-managed)
- Commands section first: exact invocations, not prose descriptions
- No duplication across tiers (`AGENTS.md`, `.cursor/rules/`, `docs/policy/`)
- No secrets, tokens, branch names, or transient details
- `Learned User Preferences` / `Learned Workspace Facts` in **both** `AGENTS.md` (cross-cutting fallback buffer) and `.cursor/rules/learned-*.mdc` (per-project) are maintained by the `agents-memory-updater` subagent — do not hand-edit
- New learned bullets are capped at **200 chars** per bullet and **12 bullets** per section
- `AGENTS.md` Skills table must reflect current `.cursor/skills/` contents
- `.cursor/rules/learned-*.mdc` files use `alwaysApply: false` with project-scoped globs and only the two `Learned ...` H2 sections
